So I used to frequent this location for years because it was on my way to my old job. The service was always kinda slow but they never screwed up my order until tonight. I’m highly allergic to dairy and I use coconut milk as a substitute, I know I clearly stated this to the guy at register but they still put milk in my coffee. I had already driven away and took a sip and couldn’t figure out why my coffee tasted weird then I realized they put milk in my coffee. Now I’m at work, very sick and can’t do anything about it. I wasn’t able to go back because I’d be late for my job. Another reason why I’m giving this place one star is because the two cashiers were not paying the costumers in line any attention and honestly didn’t seem to care very much that me and this other guy were standing there waiting. They were goofing off and laughing amongst themselves about something. I work in the service industry and I really can’t stand when people who don’t care or value their costumers. Thankfully there are many other Starbucks I frequent regularly that are wonderful and professional and understand what dietary restrictions are...thanks for the absolutely excruciating stomach ache Chevy chase Starbucks on my 12+ hour work day.

I'm a regular here, but only due to convenience. Compared to other locations where I frequent, the service here has been consistently poor for the past few years. They never seem to get it right if you order a drink with more than 1-2 simple modifications (e.g., ice amount, no. of sweetener packets). Often times, I have to track my caffeine intake for health reasons, and during my first couple years here, I'd always get a different answer every time I asked how many espresso shots come in a hot venti latte vs. iced venti latte, etc. For the most part, employees here don't seem to care, with the exception of the head barista (Lloyd, I believe). Whenever they get my drink wrong, and I complain to Lloyd, he'd make a point to address it. Aside from things they're required to do by corporate (cleanliness or music), the service is disappointing overall.
